1
00:00:00,540 --> 00:00:01,920
Greetings everyone.

2
00:00:02,600 --> 00:00:06,460
Continue work on making lab power supply.

3
00:00:06,980 --> 00:00:10,640
Now before you presented part of its schematic diagram.

4
00:00:11,300 --> 00:00:16,180
What already managed to do, so to say, in iron.

5
00:00:16,800 --> 00:00:20,800
And this part today we'll test.

6
00:00:21,800 --> 00:00:24,140
Slightly turn to schematics.

7
00:00:24,140 --> 00:00:30,500
Master generator made on microchip UC3825N.

8
00:00:31,020 --> 00:00:38,260
On its base also assembled PWM controller with feedbacks by current and by voltage.

9
00:00:38,680 --> 00:00:45,500
Now can see that current feedback not yet introduced.

10
00:00:46,080 --> 00:00:48,400
That is we'll test system without it.

11
00:00:48,400 --> 00:00:54,880
Current feedback introduced to ninth leg through resistor 1 kOhm.

12
00:00:55,120 --> 00:01:06,740
So microchip started in such connection, ninth leg through this resistor need to set on common circuit, on minus power.

13
00:01:08,040 --> 00:01:16,180
Also can see that outputs from controller go from 14th leg and from 11th.

14
00:01:16,180 --> 00:01:24,880
Schematically I marked 14th leg as one, 11th leg as two in circle.

15
00:01:25,660 --> 00:01:27,860
And now we can track control.

16
00:01:28,100 --> 00:01:31,340
One for us comes to this optical driver.

17
00:01:31,480 --> 00:01:35,460
And also see that one exits to driver diagonally.

18
00:01:36,140 --> 00:01:38,160
Also for us work keys.

19
00:01:38,380 --> 00:01:40,740
That is crosswise so work keys.

20
00:01:41,120 --> 00:01:44,500
One pair and second pair.

21
00:01:44,500 --> 00:01:53,900
Thereby we create bipolar current pulsations through primary winding of pulse transformer.

22
00:01:54,580 --> 00:02:00,500
Also can observe separate power on each of four drivers.

23
00:02:00,780 --> 00:02:03,180
Schematically marked plus-minus.

24
00:02:03,840 --> 00:02:07,900
And supplied 16 volts at these points.

25
00:02:08,460 --> 00:02:10,960
This power galvanically isolated.

26
00:02:10,960 --> 00:02:17,160
And further same power introduced separately to PWM controller itself.

27
00:02:18,960 --> 00:02:24,560
Introduced it from DC-DC converter for 5 leads.

28
00:02:25,120 --> 00:02:27,340
Schematics can find on my channel.

29
00:02:27,640 --> 00:02:31,080
And also video on its making.

30
00:02:33,900 --> 00:02:38,260
Optical connection for us also will be by voltage.

31
00:02:38,260 --> 00:02:41,700
Here visible optocoupler PC817.

32
00:02:43,100 --> 00:02:49,620
Introduced its output to first leg.

33
00:02:49,740 --> 00:02:56,620
And receives it power from 16th lead through current-limiting resistance 1 kOhm.

34
00:02:57,440 --> 00:03:09,980
This optocoupler planned to use as sensor of limited voltage of power supply, namely 1000 volts.

35
00:03:10,080 --> 00:03:20,540
That is at reaching 1000 volts at output converter should enter limiting mode to maintain this potential.

36
00:03:20,720 --> 00:03:30,680
Up to 1000 volts voltage regulation will be done with this trimmer resistance variable resistor.

37
00:03:30,680 --> 00:03:41,580
And also can observe that I picked ratings of resistors connected with variable resistance in series.

38
00:03:41,800 --> 00:03:52,740
So smooth was regulation on whole length of variable resistance rotation.

39
00:03:52,920 --> 00:03:55,680
Which very convenient for regulation.

40
00:03:55,680 --> 00:04:09,200
Also picked them so that if slider will be at extreme left position, microchip generation stops and power supply goes to standby mode.

41
00:04:09,280 --> 00:04:20,220
Can observe on scheme that PWM controller powering done from potential 16 volts that supplied to 15th lead of microchip.

42
00:04:21,110 --> 00:04:28,860
13th lead powered with voltage 12 volts, that turns out on regulator L7812.

43
00:04:29,580 --> 00:04:39,300
Done it with purpose to apply potential 12 volts to input LED of opto-drivers.

44
00:04:40,520 --> 00:04:42,320
Limit voltage.

45
00:04:42,720 --> 00:04:47,540
12 volts quite enough for these drivers and they excellently work.

46
00:04:47,540 --> 00:05:07,740
Applied this potential through current-limiting resistance 470 Ohm and also parallel to LED in driver connected resistance 1 kOhm, that excludes false trigger of opto-driver in this

47
00:05:07,740 --> 00:05:08,760
system.

48
00:05:08,760 --> 00:05:18,760
Now slightly will show how this looks in iron and further move to testing and tuning of block.

49
00:05:19,520 --> 00:05:21,120
This block in assembly.

50
00:05:22,920 --> 00:05:24,260
What can see here?

51
00:05:24,900 --> 00:05:35,240
Here I made bus by which supplied power and connection with rest of control bodies of device.

52
00:05:35,240 --> 00:05:39,340
This separable unit.

53
00:05:40,140 --> 00:05:46,360
Further DC-DC converter for 5 galvanically isolated outputs.

54
00:05:47,040 --> 00:05:51,200
4 opto-drivers HCPL3120.

55
00:05:51,780 --> 00:05:56,540
Microchip of PWM controller itself UC3825N.

56
00:05:56,800 --> 00:05:59,900
This for us regulator L7812.

57
00:06:01,820 --> 00:06:07,160
Of main strapping elements of drivers.

58
00:06:07,500 --> 00:06:10,520
These resistance chains.

59
00:06:11,460 --> 00:06:15,420
And further visible resistances 1-watt.

60
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:21,340
These chains going to FET transistor gate.

61
00:06:22,060 --> 00:06:27,920
Also here can see bundles of 15-volt zeners connected counter.

62
00:06:27,920 --> 00:06:32,300
These parts parallel to transistor leads.

63
00:06:33,420 --> 00:06:43,600
On scheme can see that one of ratings of current-limiting resistance I set.

64
00:06:43,760 --> 00:06:46,560
This 4.7 Ohm by gate.

65
00:06:47,020 --> 00:06:49,060
Second rating not yet marked.

66
00:06:50,120 --> 00:06:56,020
By default I have on board connected same resistance 4.7 Ohm.

67
00:06:56,020 --> 00:07:03,000
In practice I'll pick and if need rating of this resistance will be reduced.

68
00:07:03,740 --> 00:07:09,940
For more quality opening of FET transistor gate by leading edge.

69
00:07:10,160 --> 00:07:11,740
But this again if needed.

70
00:07:12,320 --> 00:07:21,100
This resistance is this part responsible for control of voltage potential.

71
00:07:24,500 --> 00:07:31,420
More nothing here such on which can in detail stop.

72
00:07:32,500 --> 00:07:35,200
Connected power pulse transformer.

73
00:07:38,020 --> 00:07:47,280
Decided I to make primary winding with wire in insulation, multi-strand from pure copper.

74
00:07:48,020 --> 00:07:49,940
In thermal stable insulation.

75
00:07:50,760 --> 00:07:57,960
7 turns, which corresponds at fully charged accumulator to about 14 volts.

76
00:07:58,100 --> 00:08:02,700
2 volts per turn primary winding.

77
00:08:03,060 --> 00:08:04,920
So, all ready for testing.

78
00:08:05,080 --> 00:08:10,460
Now need to look how controlled optical drivers.

79
00:08:11,370 --> 00:08:19,300
For this we'll look initial work of PWM controller at these points.

80
00:08:19,660 --> 00:08:21,140
Point 1 and point 2.

81
00:08:21,600 --> 00:08:33,280
Actually our control pulses supplied in antiphase and at their maximum duration PWM controller leaves pause between them, so-called dead time.

82
00:08:35,140 --> 00:08:38,800
Connected I oscilloscope probes at these points.

83
00:08:38,800 --> 00:08:43,260
Now apply power to DC-DC converter.

84
00:08:43,800 --> 00:08:48,080
Now will be audible sound of working core.

85
00:08:48,840 --> 00:08:56,680
And at changing pulse duration DC-DC converter will adapt to consumption and tonality of this sound will change.

86
00:08:57,880 --> 00:08:59,340
Applied I power.

87
00:09:00,740 --> 00:09:03,120
DC-DC converter started.

88
00:09:04,100 --> 00:09:08,200
See that oscillogram slightly changed.

89
00:09:08,200 --> 00:09:18,560
And now I bring slider of variable resistor out of extreme position when PWM controller doesn't do work.

90
00:09:19,200 --> 00:09:20,600
Smoothly add.

91
00:09:22,560 --> 00:09:25,980
See that appeared minimum pulse.

92
00:09:26,740 --> 00:09:32,020
And audible how DC-DC converter changed tonality.

93
00:09:32,620 --> 00:09:34,400
Such feature of it.

94
00:09:34,960 --> 00:09:41,380
Us interested how smoothly changes duration of control pulses.

95
00:09:44,000 --> 00:09:46,480
Bring to limit.

96
00:09:47,020 --> 00:09:51,340
End of resistor slider.

97
00:09:52,480 --> 00:09:57,840
And now observe, is there pause between control pulses.

98
00:09:57,840 --> 00:10:03,280
Yes, actually pause present in time.

99
00:10:05,160 --> 00:10:06,980
Now look what it is.

100
00:10:08,740 --> 00:10:12,700
Set sweep to 100 ns per cell.

101
00:10:13,940 --> 00:10:22,200
And turns out 100, 200, 300, 400 ns makes pause at this PWM controller.

102
00:10:23,200 --> 00:10:37,920
When we convinced that all works, now can look how behaves optical driver at load on FET transistor gate.

103
00:10:38,460 --> 00:10:49,160
For this I'll switch blue channel of oscilloscope to output of optical driver.

104
00:10:49,160 --> 00:10:53,800
Place it directly on FET transistor gate.

105
00:10:58,040 --> 00:11:03,900
And here we can already observe its real work under load.

106
00:11:06,920 --> 00:11:16,080
For start look how duration changes.

107
00:11:19,990 --> 00:11:22,370
Control channel yellow.

108
00:11:26,640 --> 00:11:29,860
That is optical driver works properly.

109
00:11:30,520 --> 00:11:37,580
Now can observe key opening front.

110
00:11:39,140 --> 00:11:45,540
Will need to look at front of blue channel of oscilloscope.

111
00:11:46,540 --> 00:11:50,880
Also to 100 ns per cell.

112
00:11:53,600 --> 00:12:01,180
These small interferences we can observe, this work of DC-DC converter.

113
00:12:01,440 --> 00:12:06,540
But this absolutely not critical and in no way affects work of common scheme.

114
00:12:09,800 --> 00:12:18,040
See that reducing pulse duration, front remains same.

115
00:12:23,030 --> 00:12:25,970
And can measure it in time.

116
00:12:29,300 --> 00:12:53,060
At this chain in gate circuit 4.7 Ohm and resistance 4.7 Ohm, front of signal growth on FET transistor gate makes by time 300 ns.

117
00:12:53,060 --> 00:13:05,180
And front by which controlled, very steep, that supplied precisely from PWM controller.

118
00:13:05,640 --> 00:13:08,180
Us interested precisely this parameter.

119
00:13:08,560 --> 00:13:13,420
And can also look at rear front of key closure.

120
00:13:17,290 --> 00:13:21,050
This front makes approximately 200 ns.

121
00:13:23,530 --> 00:13:34,490
Now about moment I talked, about picking this resistance that not specified.

122
00:13:34,490 --> 00:13:47,110
If we short it, now I'll do this with tweezers help, can see that front will grow.

123
00:13:48,310 --> 00:13:50,850
Steepness of front that opens.

124
00:13:54,970 --> 00:14:08,850
Visible that at shorting, with us steepness of opening front increases.

125
00:14:09,730 --> 00:14:14,190
That is from 300 ns to 200 ns.

126
00:14:15,190 --> 00:14:29,490
And means we have wide variant for picking these resistances in gate circuit to set clear work of power key.

127
00:14:30,070 --> 00:14:33,950
On this can consider check of work.

128
00:14:34,330 --> 00:14:36,570
Schemes finished, all functions.

129
00:14:37,090 --> 00:14:41,290
Such same checks should conduct on each optical driver.

130
00:14:41,390 --> 00:14:43,510
Picture should be maintained.

131
00:14:43,510 --> 00:14:46,790
So do first launch of system.

132
00:14:47,470 --> 00:14:51,730
This I recommend doing always using incandescent lamp.

133
00:14:52,290 --> 00:15:03,850
Carefully check once more whole schematics of supply wires, polarity that brought to connection of electrolytic capacitors.

134
00:15:04,010 --> 00:15:08,670
Because their reversal can lead to failure.

135
00:15:09,410 --> 00:15:16,670
And not applying power to scheme, check for start power module.

136
00:15:17,010 --> 00:15:19,910
For this connect one of wires to accumulator.

137
00:15:19,930 --> 00:15:23,130
In this case I connected minus power source.

138
00:15:23,970 --> 00:15:37,930
And plus lead, going here to capacitor battery and further to power keys, I'll connect with incandescent lamp.

139
00:15:37,930 --> 00:15:43,770
It immediately will show if we have some malfunction.

140
00:15:44,390 --> 00:15:45,910
Observe, I connect.

141
00:15:47,590 --> 00:15:51,050
And saw that lamp slightly flashed.

142
00:15:51,310 --> 00:15:57,570
And further its connection doesn't lead to filament glow.

143
00:15:58,410 --> 00:16:04,250
First flash symbolized that charged these capacities.

144
00:16:04,250 --> 00:16:16,450
And further moment that lamp doesn't burn, testifies to that power block assembled correctly and keys don't pass current without control.

145
00:16:17,690 --> 00:16:25,170
Now after we convinced of this, can move to testing of block.

146
00:16:26,390 --> 00:16:30,530
Convince that system for us off.

147
00:16:30,770 --> 00:16:37,790
That is with resistance slider help set it in non-working mode.

148
00:16:38,630 --> 00:16:44,690
Extreme position, smallest pulse duration, more precisely their full absence.

149
00:16:45,390 --> 00:16:49,250
And now connect system.

150
00:16:50,470 --> 00:16:54,310
Can use for this purpose ammeter.

151
00:16:55,070 --> 00:17:02,330
Very well with its help observe current that system consumes.

152
00:17:03,110 --> 00:17:07,510
Connect accumulator battery.

153
00:17:07,710 --> 00:17:12,290
And now can apply power to DC-DC converter.

154
00:17:14,130 --> 00:17:15,810
Power supplied.

155
00:17:16,810 --> 00:17:25,150
Say immediately, that turn count in pulse transformer quite high.

156
00:17:25,290 --> 00:17:29,570
Transformation ratio big at steep pulses.

157
00:17:29,770 --> 00:17:33,250
And voltage here will be quite high.

158
00:17:33,250 --> 00:17:46,870
Can look that now system doesn't work and discharge at us none at outputs.

159
00:17:46,990 --> 00:17:52,650
Now I shorted start green wire and end of transformer winding.

160
00:17:53,310 --> 00:17:57,850
Now I slightly add pulse duration.

161
00:18:00,890 --> 00:18:06,330
And see that appeared small discharge.

162
00:18:07,590 --> 00:18:13,530
System started, by ammeter can also control.

163
00:18:13,850 --> 00:18:15,710
Now consumption very small.

164
00:18:16,790 --> 00:18:17,850
Add more.

165
00:18:20,530 --> 00:18:21,570
Observe.

166
00:18:24,130 --> 00:18:27,170
Discharge already increased its length.

167
00:18:28,170 --> 00:18:30,850
And already stretches.

168
00:18:31,870 --> 00:18:34,870
That is system works.

169
00:18:35,770 --> 00:18:43,510
In such visual way can determine how voltage rises.

170
00:18:47,750 --> 00:18:49,470
Add more.

171
00:18:56,750 --> 00:19:04,730
Tell you guys, here far over 1000 volts at such discharge.

172
00:19:04,850 --> 00:19:09,050
At touching wires stick.

173
00:19:10,930 --> 00:19:16,790
Would still ammeter get in lens.

174
00:19:17,890 --> 00:19:19,790
Now try to do this.

175
00:19:21,450 --> 00:19:22,530
So.

176
00:19:23,670 --> 00:19:25,750
So was visible.

177
00:19:25,910 --> 00:19:26,790
Scale at zero.

178
00:19:42,050 --> 00:19:43,750
Bad slightly contact.

179
00:19:43,830 --> 00:19:44,910
Here now is.

180
00:19:49,010 --> 00:19:58,370
We see that at shorting consumption reaches 9 amps current.

181
00:19:59,530 --> 00:20:02,350
Add more pulse duration.

182
00:20:09,790 --> 00:20:12,470
10 amps short.

183
00:20:14,130 --> 00:20:16,850
Add already full duration.

184
00:20:18,750 --> 00:20:22,370
Probably now will be specific discharge.

185
00:20:24,770 --> 00:20:29,770
With this matter already need to be more careful.

186
00:20:32,970 --> 00:20:42,110
Better such experiments conduct through lamp bulb so system didn't fail.

187
00:20:46,210 --> 00:20:48,430
You see all yourselves.

188
00:20:50,950 --> 00:20:54,290
Hellish power at this system.

189
00:21:02,100 --> 00:21:05,440
Switch to off mode.

190
00:21:07,400 --> 00:21:13,160
Now will interest us tuning of this system by frequency.

191
00:21:13,280 --> 00:21:15,500
For this we need oscilloscope.

192
00:21:16,280 --> 00:21:23,920
Look oscillogram on one of transformer leads relative to start lead.

193
00:21:24,140 --> 00:21:27,300
And already tune to optimal frequency.

194
00:21:27,300 --> 00:21:30,900
Tune core under operating frequency.

195
00:21:32,260 --> 00:21:37,300
For this I connected yellow channel of oscilloscope to one of leads.

196
00:21:37,380 --> 00:21:41,980
Namely to third lead of transformer, since voltage here high.

197
00:21:43,720 --> 00:21:47,320
If count from start of winding.

198
00:21:48,560 --> 00:21:52,460
Probes I have at 1500 volts, hundredfold suppression.

199
00:21:52,620 --> 00:21:54,960
So not afraid for device.

200
00:21:54,960 --> 00:22:04,380
If you have probes of tenfold suppression, this better do by first lead.

201
00:22:05,500 --> 00:22:10,000
Now power supplied to keys from accumulator.

202
00:22:10,180 --> 00:22:14,420
And now apply power to DC-DC converter.

203
00:22:15,420 --> 00:22:25,240
At that resistance slider responsible for pulse duration switched to system off.

204
00:22:26,320 --> 00:22:30,480
Apply power to converter.

205
00:22:30,840 --> 00:22:36,180
And see for now at transformer output nothing.

206
00:22:36,340 --> 00:22:41,860
Now smoothly add duration of control pulses.

207
00:22:45,230 --> 00:22:47,870
And see such picture.

208
00:22:47,990 --> 00:22:55,850
With increasing duration can observe that quantity of these waves also increases.

209
00:22:56,330 --> 00:23:02,850
This means our core is not in optimal operating mode.

210
00:23:03,250 --> 00:23:06,170
Pulse duration to full.

211
00:23:06,790 --> 00:23:11,430
And we can count quantity of these waves.

212
00:23:11,430 --> 00:23:13,690
1, 2, 3, 4, 5.

213
00:23:14,310 --> 00:23:18,830
That is approximately we need to raise frequency 5 times.

214
00:23:19,690 --> 00:23:21,510
For this transformer.

215
00:23:23,270 --> 00:23:24,930
This will now do.

216
00:23:29,260 --> 00:23:36,100
This resistance answers on scheme for frequency.

217
00:23:36,360 --> 00:23:41,180
At ratings presented on scheme.

218
00:23:42,180 --> 00:23:49,660
This 10 kOhm at fifth leg and 2200 pF seventh leg.

219
00:23:50,940 --> 00:23:57,300
Frequency will regulate from 35 kHz to 185 kHz.

220
00:23:58,240 --> 00:23:59,700
At this PWM controller.

221
00:24:00,100 --> 00:24:02,880
And raise frequency.

222
00:24:03,160 --> 00:24:09,540
Observe how phenomenon of ringing in transformer will disappear.

223
00:24:12,320 --> 00:24:16,040
This such preliminary tuning.

224
00:24:16,920 --> 00:24:20,140
Further, after connection of diode bridge.

225
00:24:21,200 --> 00:24:25,640
Will be conducted correction of transformer work.

226
00:24:25,720 --> 00:24:29,720
Directly under load by DC.

227
00:24:30,720 --> 00:24:34,680
Now we'll remove this negative phenomenon.

228
00:24:36,780 --> 00:24:38,080
Of oscillations.

229
00:24:38,480 --> 00:24:39,660
Frequency raise.

230
00:24:39,660 --> 00:24:50,660
We need so was one pulse each.

231
00:24:51,920 --> 00:24:54,560
Power supply slightly grumbles.

232
00:24:55,840 --> 00:25:00,980
Since doesn't withstand consumption of DC-DC converter.

233
00:25:01,160 --> 00:25:01,660
But nothing.

234
00:25:03,880 --> 00:25:05,760
So we bring.

235
00:25:11,010 --> 00:25:16,810
And here practically already what we need.

236
00:25:18,710 --> 00:25:23,590
Now can control pulse duration.

237
00:25:25,350 --> 00:25:28,230
From zero to maximum.

238
00:25:30,970 --> 00:25:35,150
Oscillogram became significantly more beautiful.

239
00:25:36,150 --> 00:25:41,670
Now need to connect at these points load.

240
00:25:42,170 --> 00:25:44,910
And look what signal form will be under load.

241
00:25:44,990 --> 00:25:51,190
Connected I lamp 60 W at 220 Volts.

242
00:25:52,390 --> 00:25:57,030
And on it we'll observe oscillogram and voltage.

243
00:25:58,550 --> 00:26:00,790
Parallel its output.

244
00:26:00,790 --> 00:26:02,090
Apply power.

245
00:26:03,990 --> 00:26:08,290
And smoothly add duration of control pulses.

246
00:26:13,800 --> 00:26:17,000
See that lamp spiral starts to glow.

247
00:26:18,660 --> 00:26:19,520
Go further.

248
00:26:25,500 --> 00:26:27,360
Oscillogram changes.

249
00:26:27,840 --> 00:26:35,580
And here maximum duration of control pulses.

250
00:26:36,580 --> 00:26:38,660
Such have oscillogram.

251
00:26:40,520 --> 00:26:42,980
Need to look at its symmetry.

252
00:26:43,140 --> 00:26:45,680
See symmetric work.

253
00:26:47,900 --> 00:26:52,460
Smooth regulation if we rotate slider.

254
00:26:54,300 --> 00:26:56,080
Output voltage.

255
00:26:57,520 --> 00:27:05,800
At this stage can consider preliminary tuning of system finished.

256
00:27:06,980 --> 00:27:13,420
